=== ATP Accounting


Direct yield: +2 ATP (net) and +2 NADH (~+5 ATP when oxidized via the malate-aspartate shuttle or glycerol-3-phosphate shuttle). Gated yield: ~30 ATP, because glycolysis produces the pyruvate that feeds PDC, TCA, and the ETC. When glycolysis is impaired the whole downstream chain starves; when it is upregulated as a fallback (under hypoxia or ETC dysfunction), only the +2 direct ATP is retained and ~25 ATP of aerobic capacity is lost.

